'''Bara Sapoko Ndiaye''' (born 31 December 2007) is a Senegalese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Bundesliga|German Bundesliga]] club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], on loan from [[The Gambia|Gambian]] club Gambinos Stars, and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Ndiaye was born in [[Meckhe]], Senegal,<ref>{{Kicker|bara-sapoko-ndiaye|access-date=25 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ericfavretv.com/de-mekhe-au-bayern-le-parcours-de-bara-sapoko-ndiaye-la-nouvelle-pepite-de-munich/|title=De Mékhé au Bayern: Le parcours de Bara Sapoko Ndiaye, la nouvelle pépite de Munich… |language=fr|website=ericfavretv.com|date=15 April 2026|access-date=25 April 2026}}</ref> and started his youth career with Thiès and Senegal Elite Stars.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/articles/football-bara-sapoko-ndiaye-the-new-gem-of-bayern-munich |title=Football: Bara Sapoko Ndiaye, the new gem of Bayern Munich |publisher=SportNewsAfrica|date=11 April 2026|access-date=25 April 2026}}</ref> After his stint in Senegal, he joined the [[Youth system|youth academy]] of [[The Gambia|Gambian]] side Gambinos Stars.<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|new_id=pe1920460/bara-sapoko-ndiaye}}</ref><ref>{{Soccerway|new_id=ndiaye-bara/QNiKiuQb |accessdate=25 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.seneweb.com/fr/news/Sport/bayern-munich-bara-sapoko-ndiayes-debut-sparks-a-money-war-in-senegal_n_489556.html|title=Bayern Munich : les débuts de Bara Sapoko Ndiaye déclenchent une "guerre d’argent" au Sénégal |language=fr|website=seneweb.com|access-date=25 April 2026}}</ref>

====Loan to Bayern Munich====
In January 2026, three years after [[Red&Gold Football]], the joint venture between German [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and American [[Major League Soccer]] (MLS) club [[Los Angeles FC]] became partners with Gambinos Stars back in 2023,<ref>{{Cite web |title= Red&Gold Football partners with Gambinos Stars Africa for talent development in West Africa |url=https://rg-football.com/en/blog/red-gold-football-partners-with-gambinos-stars-africa-for-talent-development-in-west-africa |website=Red&Gold Football | date = 25 September 2023 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title= Red&Gold Football partners with Gambinos Stars Africa for talent development in West Africa |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/09/red-gold-football-cooperates-with-elite-academy-in-west-africa |website=FC Bayern Munich | date =  25 September 2023 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=25 September 2023 |title=Red&Gold Football Partners With Gambinos Stars Africa For Talent Development In West Africa |url=https://www.lafc.com/news/red-gold-football-partners-with-gambinos-stars-africa-for-talent-development-in- |website=Los Angeles FC}}</ref> Ndiaye moved to Germany and joined Bayern Munich on loan for the rest of the [[2025–26 FC Bayern Munich season|2025–26 season]], after previously having trialed with [[Swiss Super League]] side [[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshopper]] in 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title= El FC Bayern ficha a Bara Sapoko Ndiaye, cedido por el Gambinos Stars Africa |url=https://fcbayern.com/es/noticias/2026/01/el-fc-bayern-ficha-a-bara-sapoko-ndiaye-cedido-por-el-gambinos-stars-africa |website=FC Bayern Munich |language=es | date = 3 January 2026 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title = FC Bayern leiht Bara Sapoko Ndiaye aus |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/fc-bayern-leiht-bara-sapoko-ndiaye-aus-35379 |website=Bundesliga |language= de | date = 3 January 2026 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/fc-bayern-neuzugang-aus-gambia-hat-ein-spiel-verbot-folgenschwere-einschraenkung-69593548cf4737ac6059af5f |title=Bayern-Neuzugang hat ein Spiel-Verbot! |language=de|publisher=[[Bild]] |date=5 January 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wetterauer-zeitung.de/sport/fussball/so-will-der-fc-bayern-das-spielverbot-von-neuzugang-ndiaye-umgehen-zr-94110213.html|title=So will der FC Bayern das Spielverbot von seinem Neuzugang umgehen|trans-title=This is how FC Bayern wants to circumvent the playing ban of their new signing|language=de|publisher={{ill|Wetterauer Zeitung|de}}|date=6 January 2026|access-date=8 January 2026}}</ref>

He made his professional debut with Bayern Munich on 11 April 2026, during a 5–0 away win Bundesliga match against [[FC St. Pauli]], substituting [[Jamal Musiala]] in the second half.<ref>{{Cite web |title= Torrekord & 12 Punkte Vorsprung! FC Bayern jubelt auch beim FC St. Pauli |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/profis/bundesliga/2025-2026/fc-st-pauli-fc-bayern-muenchen-11-04-2026/spielbericht |language=de|website=FC Bayern Munich | date = 11 April 2026 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=11 April 2026 |title=FC St. Pauli - Bayern München 0:5 |url=https://www.kicker.de/st-pauli-gegen-bayern-2026-bundesliga-5051009/spielinfo |language=de|website=Kicker}}</ref> Eight days later, on April 19, Ndiaye won the [[2025–26 Bundesliga]] and the 35th league title with Bayern Munich, substituting [[Raphaël Guerreiro]] at the 78th minute of a 4–2 home win over [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c89558d5d5nt |title=Bayern Munich 4–2 Stuttgart |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 April 2026 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/bayern-gegen-stuttgart-2026-bundesliga-5051012/spielbericht |title=Bayern dreht nach Rückstand auf und kürt sich vorzeitig zum Deutschen Meister |publisher=Kicker|language = de | date = 19 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sofascore.com/sv/football/match/vfb-stuttgart-fc-bayern-munchen/xdbsCdb#id:14065222 | title = Bayern-Stuttgart |publisher=Sofascore | language = en | date = 19 April 2026 | access-date = 19 April 2026}}</ref> Six days later he made his first start, during a 4–3 comeback away win Bundesliga match against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]], on 25 April.<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 April 2026 |title= 4:3 nach 0:3! Bayern bezw |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/profis/bundesliga/2025-2026/1-fsv-mainz-05-fc-bayern-muenchen-25-04-2026/spielbericht |language=de|website=FC Bayern Munich}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/mainz-gegen-bayern-2026-bundesliga-5051022/spielbericht |title=Joker bringen die Wende: Bayern drehen in Mainz nach der Pause auf |publisher=Kicker|language = de | date=25 April 2026 | access-date = 27 April 2026}}</ref> Ndiaye made his second start with the club seven days later, during a 3–3 home draw Bundesliga match against [[1. FC Heidenheim]], on 2 May.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 May 2026 |title= Vom Last-Minute-Ausgleich zur Extra-Power: Was das 3:3 gegen Heidenheim für unser Duell mit Paris bedeutet |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2026/05/nachbericht-bundesliga-fc-bayern-1-fc-heidenheim |language=de|website=FC Bayern Munich}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/bayern-gegen-heidenheim-2026-bundesliga-5051030/spielbericht |title=Ramaj im Pech: Bayern gleichen ganz spät gegen Heidenheim noch aus |publisher=Kicker|language= de | date=2 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
In May 2026, Ndiaye was called up by [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]] head coach [[Pape Thiaw]] to the preliminary squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] between 11 June – 19 July 2026 and the pre-tournament [[Exhibition game#International football|friendlies]] against [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] and [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] on 31 May and 9 June 2026; respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mondial 2026: Pape Thiaw publie sa liste |url=https://fsfoot.sn/mondial-2026-pape-thiaw-publie-sa-liste/ |access-date=21 May 2026 |publisher=[[Senegalese Football Federation|Fédération Sénégalaise de Football]] |date=21 May 2026 |language=French}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Sapoko Ndiaye plays as a [[midfielder]]. Senegalese news website ''OnzeD'Afrik'' wrote in 2026 that he "stands out for his stamina, his ability to get forward, and his tactical intelligence".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onzedafrik.com/bara-sapoko-ndiaye-bayern-munich/|title=Bara Sapoko Ndiaye : Le jeune prodige sénégalais séduit le Bayern|trans-title=Bara Sapoko Ndiaye: The young Senegalese prodigy impresses Bayern|language=fr|publisher=OnzeD'Afrik|date=6 January 2026|access-date=8 January 2026}}</ref>

